Rev. Elera Wisdom Ngofa, Head Pastor, Victory Family, Christian Pentecostal Mission (CPM), Ketu, Lagos, has called on Nigerian youths to contest for elective positions in the coming 2023 general elections. Elera, the CPM’s Area G. Supervisor, gave the admonition when he spoke to newsmen on the sideline of his church’s 25th anniversary, termed ‘Greater Glory’. He lamented that the nation‘s leadership had not been performing well, while calling the youths to take up the mantle to save the country from its current doldrums. Adeboye, A Great Blessing To Humanity – CAN, PFN Lagos Catholic Faithful To Honour First Indigenous Bishop The cleric lamented that the leaders had not been ruling the nation well, stressing, “They are not doing much. There is injustice in the land. Instead of fulfilling their promises, they abandon their leadership role. “The leaders, especially the political class, must be sincere with the people. They are not honouring their pledges.” He urged them to shun selfishness and show total commitment to the people and work for the good of the nation.